ddle Ages, often represented in miracle plays. The name has been perennially popular among English speakers since the 16th century and has been particularly favoured since the 1980s."],"variants":[{"name":"Danyal","meanings":["Fanciful respelling of   Daniel ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":6,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":15,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Daniel Fisc II was born on 1 May 1208, in Laxfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Daniel Fisc I, was 38 and his mother, Mrs Daniel Fisc, was 28. He had at least 2 sons with Agnes. He died in 1258, in Laxfield, Suffolk, England, at the age of 50, and was buried in Laxfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1 May 1208–1258":"1. mai 1208–1258","1208–1258":"1208–1258","1207–Female":"1207–Surnud","1235–Male":"1235–Surnud","1250–1305":"1250–1305","1170–1208":"1170–1208","1181–Female":"1181–Surnud","1305":"1305","1215":"1215","LIV. 1 MAY 1208":"1. mai 1208","1258":"1258","1 May 1208":"1. mai 1208","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1250":"1250","1181":"1181","1170":"1170","1208":"1208","1207":"1207","Laxfield, Suffolk, England":"Laxfield, Suffolk, England","of Laxfield, Suffolk, Eng":"Laxfield, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","All Saints Churchyard Laxfield, Mid S